\subsection{Cover-totality Ext-transport at universe $u$ (iter-033)}

Iter-032 closed the cover-totality Ext-transport \emph{at universe $u+1$}, landing on the right-hand side $\HModule\,k\,F\,n$. To exploit the iter-029/iter-030 LES (which lives at universe $u$, by iter-014's $\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,X : \Type\,u$ ascription), we also need the parallel transport \emph{at universe $u$} — turning the iter-031 source-object iso into a $k$-linear equivalence between $\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,T$ (at universe $u$, definitionally $\Ext_u\,X_1\,F\,n$ for $X_1$ the sheafified-yoneda source) and $\Ext_u\,X_2\,F\,n$ for $X_2 = (\constantSheaf\,J\,\_).\mathrm{obj}\,(\ModuleCat.\mathrm{of}\,k\,k)$.

The body is exactly the same shape as iter-032's $\HModule\,\mathtt{\_top\_linearEquiv}$, but at the unmarked universe of $\HModulePrime$. Because the LHS is $\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,T$ (forcing $\Ext_u$), Lean's universe inference picks the $u$-flavour of every $\Ext$-API piece in the body — $\Ext.\mathtt{mk\_0}$, $\Ext.\mathtt{precompOfLinear}$, $\Ext.\mathtt{comp\_assoc\_of\_second\_deg\_zero}$, $\Ext.\mathtt{mk\_0\_comp\_mk\_0}$, $\Ext.\mathtt{mk\_0\_id\_comp}$ are all universe-polymorphic and adapt automatically.

The iter-033 result intentionally does \emph{not} touch the universe bridge to $\HModule$ — that final piece (which involves upgrading Mathlib's $\Ext.\mathtt{chgUniv} : \Ext_w\,X\,Y\,n \cong \Ext_{w'}\,X\,Y\,n$ from a bare $\Equiv$ to a $\LinearEquiv$, plus composition with iter-032's $\HModule\,\mathtt{\_top\_linearEquiv}$) is iter-034+ work. By splitting Step 3 into a cover-totality piece (iter-031/032/033) plus a universe-bump piece (iter-034+), each iteration appends one declaration.

\begin{definition}[Cover-totality Ext-transport at universe $u$, iter-033]
  \label{def:Scheme_HModule_prime_top_linearEquiv}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.HModule'_top_linearEquiv}
  \uses{def:Scheme_HModule_prime_top_sourceIso, def:Scheme_HModule_prime}
  \leanok
  Let $k$ be a field, $C$ a category with morphism universe $u$, $J : \GrothendieckTopology\,C$, $T : C$ a terminal object (witnessed by $h_T : \mathtt{IsTerminal}\,T$), and assume $\HasWeakSheafify\,J\,(\Type\,u)$, $\HasSheafify\,J\,(\ModuleCat.\{u\}\,k)$, and $\HasExt\,(\Sheaf\,J\,(\ModuleCat.\{u\}\,k))$. There is a $k$-linear isomorphism
  \[
    \HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,T
    \;\equiv_{\Module k}\;
    \Ext\bigl(
      (\constantSheaf\,J\,\_).\mathrm{obj}\,(\ModuleCat.\mathrm{of}\,k\,k),\; F,\; n
    \bigr).
  \]
  Both sides live at $\Type\,u$ (the $\HModulePrime$ universe of iter-014); the $\Ext$ on the right is the $u$-flavour, distinct from iter-009's $\HModule\,k\,F\,n : \Type\,(u+1)$.
\end{definition}

\begin{proof}
  \leanok
  Let $\alpha$ denote the iter-031 source-object iso $\HModulePrimeTopSourceIso\,k\,h_T$, with $\alpha.\mathtt{hom} : X_1 \to X_2$ and $\alpha.\mathtt{inv} : X_2 \to X_1$ in $\Sheaf\,J\,(\ModuleCat.\{u\}\,k)$, where $X_1$ is the sheafified-yoneda source on $T$ and $X_2 = (\constantSheaf\,J\,\_).\mathrm{obj}\,(\ModuleCat.\mathrm{of}\,k\,k)$. By iter-014, $\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,T = \Ext\,X_1\,F\,n$ (at universe $u$); the desired equivalence $\Ext\,X_1\,F\,n \equiv_{\Module k} \Ext\,X_2\,F\,n$ is built via $\mathtt{LinearEquiv.ofLinear}$ from the forward map $(\Ext.\mathtt{mk\_0}\,\alpha.\mathtt{inv}).\mathtt{precompOfLinear}\,k\,F\,(0+n=n)$ and the inverse map $(\Ext.\mathtt{mk\_0}\,\alpha.\mathtt{hom}).\mathtt{precompOfLinear}\,k\,F\,(0+n=n)$. Each round-trip closes with the four-step rewrite (associativity in reverse via $\Ext.\mathtt{comp\_assoc\_of\_second\_deg\_zero}$, composition collapse via $\Ext.\mathtt{mk\_0\_comp\_mk\_0}$, the iso identity $\alpha.\mathtt{inv\_hom\_id}$ or $\alpha.\mathtt{hom\_inv\_id}$, and identity-elimination via $\Ext.\mathtt{mk\_0\_id\_comp}$). Plan-agent $\mathtt{lean\_run\_code}$ probe (iter-033 pass) confirms the body typechecks and produces kernel-only axioms $[\propext, \mathtt{Classical.choice}, \mathtt{Quot.sound}]$.
\end{proof}

\subsection{Use in Serre finiteness}

The iter-029 lemmas materialise Step 1 (the abstract LES) and Step 2 (the corner-identification simp lemmas) of the iter-028 Serre-finiteness sketch (Section~\ref{sec:scheme_affineCoverMVSquare}); iter-030 materialised Step 2.5 (the toModuleKSheaf specialisation, a routine binding so downstream code paths can reference the LES on the structure sheaf of a curve directly); iter-031 materialised the \emph{source-object} half of Step 3 (the cover-totality identification at the sheaf level); iter-032 materialised the \emph{Ext-transport} half of Step 3 at universe $u+1$ (landing on $\HModule\,k\,F\,n$); iter-033 (this iteration) materialises the parallel \emph{Ext-transport} at universe $u$ (landing on $\Ext_u\,X_2\,F\,n$ for $X_2 = (\constantSheaf\,J\,\_).\mathrm{obj}\,(\ModuleCat.\mathrm{of}\,k\,k)$, so that the iter-029/iter-030 LES at universe $u$ feeds directly into it). The remaining work — Step 3-finish (the universe-bump $\Ext_u\,X_2\,F\,n \equiv_{\Module k} \Ext_{u+1}\,X_2\,F\,n = \HModule\,k\,F\,n$, requiring an upgrade of Mathlib's $\Ext.\mathtt{chgUniv}$ from $\Equiv$ to $\LinearEquiv$, iter-034+), Step 4 (affine vanishing $H^{>0}(\Spec A, \mathcal F) = 0$, possibly multi-iteration depending on Mathlib state), and Step 5 (finiteness of each $H^0$ piece, hence of $H^1(C, \mathcal O_C)$) — is iter-034+.

